trans-unit.source: A flow content element that defines a cell of content within a <xref href="System.Windows.Documents.Table"></xref>.
The TableCell element is the only table element that directly hosts content.

Other table elements (<xref:System.Windows.Documents.Table>, <xref:System.Windows.Documents.TableColumn>, <xref:System.Windows.Documents.TableRowGroup>, and <xref:System.Windows.Documents.TableRow>) exist to define the structural attributes of a table.
TableCell elements may host one or more flow content elements deriving from <xref:System.Windows.Documents.Block>.

Valid content elements for a TableCell include: - <xref:System.Windows.Documents.BlockUIContainer> - <xref:System.Windows.Documents.List> - <xref:System.Windows.Documents.Paragraph> - <xref:System.Windows.Documents.Section> - <xref:System.Windows.Documents.Table> The <xref:System.Windows.Documents.TableCellCollection> collection class provides facilities for working with collections of TableCell objects.
> [!NOTE] > There is no built in data binding for the contents of a TableCell.

The simplest option for adding data binding functionality to a TableCell is to put a data bound <xref:System.Windows.Controls.TextBlock> in your TableCell like this: `<TableCell><InlineUIContainer><TextBlock Text="{Binding ...}" /></InlineUIContainer></TableCell>`
Initializes a new, empty instance of the <xref href="System.Windows.Documents.TableCell"></xref> class.

Initializes a new instance of the <xref href="System.Windows.Documents.TableCell"></xref> class, taking a specified <xref href="System.Windows.Documents.Block"></xref> object as the initial contents of the new <xref href="System.Windows.Documents.TableCell"></xref>.
A <xref href="System.Windows.Documents.Block"></xref> object specifying the initial contents of the new <xref href="System.Windows.Documents.TableCell"></xref>.

Gets a <xref href="System.Windows.Documents.BlockCollection"></xref> containing the top-level <xref href="System.Windows.Documents.Block"></xref> elements that comprise the contents of the <xref href="System.Windows.Documents.TableCell"></xref>.
Use the <xref:System.Windows.Documents.BlockCollection> returned by this property to enumerate or manipulate the contents of a <xref:System.Windows.Documents.TableCell> element.

A <xref href="System.Windows.Documents.BlockCollection"></xref> containing the <xref href="System.Windows.Documents.Block"></xref> elements that comprise the contents of the <xref href="System.Windows.Documents.TableCell"></xref> This property has no default value.
Gets or sets a <xref href="System.Windows.Media.Brush"></xref> to use when painting the element's border.
For a table of swatches that show the available pre-defined brush colors, see <xref:System.Windows.Media.Brushes>.
## Dependency Property Information ||| |-|-| |Identifier field|| |Metadata properties set to `true`||
The brush used to apply to the element's border.
The default value is a **null** brush.
Identifies the <xref:System.Windows.Documents.TableCell.BorderBrush*> dependency property.
To be added.
Gets or sets the border thickness for the element.
## XAML Attribute Usage ``` - or - - or - - or - ``` ## XAML Values *uniformThickness* String representation of a single value to apply uniformly to all four thickness dimensions.
For example, a value of `"10"` is equivalent to a value of `"10,10,10,10"`.
An unqualified value is measured in device independent pixels.
Strings need not explicitly include decimal points.
*independentThickness* String representation of four ordered <xref:System.Double> values corresponding to independent thickness dimensions for left, top, right, and bottom, in this order.
The four values must be separated with commas; spaces are not allowed.

For example, "5,10,15,20" results in 5 pixels of border to the left of content, 10 pixels of border above content, 15 pixels of border to the right of content, and 20 pixels of border below the content.
*qualifiedUniformThickness* A value described by *uniformThickness* followed by one of the following unit specifiers: `px`, `in`.
`px` (default) is [!INCLUDE[TLA#tla_dipixel#plural](~/add/includes/ajax-current-ext-md.md)] `in` is inches; 1in==96px For example, `"1in"` provides uniform border of 1 inch in all directions.
*qualifiedIndependentThickness* A value described by *independentThickness*, with each independent value followed by one of the following unit specifiers: `px`, `in`.
`px` (default) is [!INCLUDE[TLA#tla_dipixel#plural](~/add/includes/ajax-current-ext-md.md)] `in` is inches; 1in==96px For example, `"1.5in,0.8in,1.5in,0.8in"`.
Unit specifiers may be mixed or omitted from one or more values.
## Dependency Property Information ||| |-|-| |Identifier field|| |Metadata properties set to `true`||
A <xref href="System.Windows.Thickness"></xref> structure specifying the amount of border to apply, in device independent pixels.
The default value is a uniform thickness of zero (**0.0**).
Identifies the <xref:System.Windows.Documents.TableCell.BorderThickness*> dependency property.
To be added.
Gets or sets the number of columns that the <xref href="System.Windows.Documents.TableCell"></xref> should span.
## Dependency Property Information ||| |-|-| |Identifier field|| |Metadata properties set to `true`||
The number of columns the <xref href="System.Windows.Documents.TableCell"></xref> should span.
The default value is **1** (no spanning).
Identifies the <xref:System.Windows.Documents.TableCell.ColumnSpan*> dependency property.
To be added.
Gets or sets a value that specifies the relative direction for flow of content within a <xref href="System.Windows.Documents.TableCell"></xref> element.
The flow direction of content typically corresponds to the innate flow direction of the language being represented.
Hebrew and Arabic provide examples of languages that naturally flow from right-to-left.
English, German, and Russian provide examples of languages that naturally flow from left-to-right.
**Note:** The value of this property is not automatically changed to match the language used by the operating system.
If you need to use a different value then the default of <xref:System.Windows.FlowDirection>, you must specify it yourself.
## Dependency Property Information ||| |-|-| |Identifier field|| |Metadata properties set to `true`|, |
A member of the <xref href="System.Windows.FlowDirection"></xref> enumeration specifying the relative flow direction.
Getting this property returns the currently effective flow direction.
Setting this property causes the contents of the <xref href="System.Windows.Documents.TableCell"></xref> element to re-flow in the indicated direction.
The default value is <xref href="System.Windows.FlowDirection"></xref>.
Identifies the <xref:System.Windows.Documents.TableCell.FlowDirection*> dependency property.
To be added.
Gets or sets the height of each line of content.
Changing this value does not change the height of the associated text; rather, it changes the height of the line that contains the text.
In addition to this property, the layout of lines in a <xref:System.Windows.Documents.TableCell> is affected by its <xref:System.Windows.Documents.TableCell.LineStackingStrategy%2A> property.
## XAML Attribute Usage ``` - or - - or - ``` ## XAML Values *double* String representation of a value equal to or greater than `0.0034` and equal to or less then `160000`.
An unqualified value is measured in device independent pixels.
Strings need not explicitly include decimal points.
*qualifiedDouble* A *double* value as described above, (excepting `Auto`) followed by one of the following unit specifiers: `px`, `in`, `cm`, `pt`.

`px` (default) is [!INCLUDE[TLA#tla_dipixel#plural](~/add/includes/ajax-current-ext-md.md)] `in` is inches; 1in==96px `cm` is centimeters; 1cm==(96/2.54) px `pt` is points; 1pt==(96/72) px Auto Causes the line height to be determined automatically from the current font characteristics.
Equivalent to a property value of <xref:System.Double.NaN>.
## Dependency Property Information ||| |-|-| |Identifier field|| |Metadata properties set to `true`|, , |
A double value specifying the height of line in device independent pixels.
LineHeight must be equal to or greater than `0.0034` and equal to or less then `160000`.
A value of <xref:System.Double> (equivalent to an attribute value of "`Auto`") causes the line height to be determined automatically from the current font characteristics.
The default value is <xref:System.Double>.
Raised if an attempt is made to set <xref:System.Windows.Controls.TextBlock.LineHeight*> to a non-positive value.
Identifies the <xref:System.Windows.Documents.TableCell.LineHeight*> dependency property.
To be added.
Gets or sets the mechanism by which a line box is determined for each line of text within the <xref href="System.Windows.Documents.TableCell"></xref>.
## Dependency Property Information ||| |-|-| |Identifier field|| |Metadata properties set to `true`|, , |
The mechanism by which a line box is determined for each line of text within the <xref href="System.Windows.Documents.TableCell"></xref>.
The default value is <xref href="System.Windows.LineStackingStrategy"></xref>.
Identifies the <xref:System.Windows.Documents.TableCell.LineStackingStrategy*> dependency property.
To be added.
Creates and returns an <xref href="System.Windows.Automation.Peers.AutomationPeer"></xref> object for this <xref href="System.Windows.Documents.TableCell"></xref>.
This method overrides <xref:System.Windows.ContentElement.OnCreateAutomationPeer%2A>.
An <xref href="System.Windows.Automation.Peers.AutomationPeer"></xref> object for this <xref href="System.Windows.Documents.TableCell"></xref>.

Gets or sets a value that indicates the horizontal alignment of text content.
